Here's a JavaScript function that uses regular expressions to extract the three-character code from a given filename in the specified format:
```javascript
function extractCode(filename) {
  const regex = /^[0-9A-Za-z]{2,3}(?=\.[a-zA-Z]{3}\.usfm$/;
  const match = filename.match(regex);
  return match ? match[0].slice(0, 3);
}
```
